To download Loop Master Workspace and open it in xCode, run this script.

Note, everything from the /bin to the )" must be on one line, all together, no extra spaces or returns.
Open terminal
Copy/Paste this code into terminal:


/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/loopnlearn/LoopBuildScripts/main/BuildLoopMaster.sh)"


Once it opens in xCode, wait for indexing to finish (top line).
Indexing could take 30 seconds, it might take an hour.   Wait it out.

then follow the "Using Workspace" section of LoopDocs.

https://loopkit.github.io/loopdocs/build/loopworkspace/#using-loopworkspace

